{"tid":1907144,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"環保少女英國搞遊行 萬幾人踩爛晒塊地","createTime":"2020-03-02T11:52:52.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-05T15:46:18.000Z","uid":41906,"like":11,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":12,"replies":[{"pid":"b7bf11c48568d3b644429b1cfbdfb4b0ce6f6dba","tid":1907144,"uid":41906,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-02T11:52:52.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/660/cpsprodpb/14077/production/_111093028_photo-2020-02-28-12-35-21.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F660%2Fcpsprodpb%2F14077%2Fproduction%2F_111093028_photo-2020-02-28-12-35-21.jpg&h=25638480&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n事源Greta Thunberg早兩日在布里斯托一間大學有演講，之後萬幾人在校內草地遊行，大量人群加上當時落雨踩到塊地變晒泥濘<br />\n<br />\nBBC Source<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-bristol-51696203\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-bristol-51696203&d=FoM%2FNT%2BxDvRLDdkWKwCN%2BPG%2BV2qV11Yco%2FuAlnZU2is%3D&h=e4ef1334\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-bristol-51696203&h=fe37a2ca\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-bristol-51696203</a><br />\n<br />\nGreta Thunberg Bristol strike: Row over College Green damage<br />\n<br />\nHundreds have called for the organisers of a Greta Thunberg climate change rally to pay for damage caused to green space.<br />\n<br />\nAround 15,000 people are believed to have attended Friday's Bristol Youth Strike 4 Climate rally, churning up College Green and angering many.<br />\n<br />\nA fundraiser was set up for repairs, which then resulted in calls for rally organisers to cover the costs.<br />\n<br />\nThe organiser said people had done their best in the muddy conditions.<br />\n<br />\nClimate campaigner Greta gave a speech on College Green before leading a march around the city.<br />\n<br />\nThe combination of thousands of people and heavy rain turned much of the grass into mud, angering some.<br />\n<br />\nGavin Mountjoy commented on Facebook: &quot;Oh the irony, hundreds of people turning up to talk about our planet dying end up destroying a green area.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nBarrie Moore, also on Facebook, said: &quot;The organisers of this march should be made to pay for the damage.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nGreta Thunberg in Bristol: How it happened<br />\nJon Usher, head of partnerships of Bristol-based charity Sustrans, set up a GoFundMe page after the march ended, aiming to raise &pound;20,000.<br />\n<br />\nBy Sunday morning more than &pound;9,000 had been donated.<br />\n<br />\nMr Usher, who attended the rally, said: &quot;I did it knowing how important the green is to our staff as a place to go in the spring and summertime.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;I thought it would be nice to give something back to the city.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nBristol City Council, which is responsible for College Green, said it will examine the area on Monday.<br />\n<br />\nKai Damani, one of the event's organisers, said people had done their best in the conditions.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;When you look at College Green now, most of it is completely brown but where the flowers are is completely intact which does show that people do care about wildlife,&quot; he said.<br />\n<br />\nAvon and Somerset Police had raised safety concerns before the event, but Supt Andy Bennett praised the organisers afterwards.<br />\n<br />\nHe said: &quot;I think it's been a great success for the city and a great success for the organisers.&quot;"},{"pid":"1d3da23243391b076b337f6632c628910e135a44","tid":1907144,"uid":41423,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-03-02T11:54:20.000Z","msg":"蠔爹油"},{"pid":"fe9581f10876c898a60f34d846ad3ad0d1904ce0","tid":1907144,"uid":182127,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-02T11:54:36.000Z","msg":"戇鳩閪"},{"pid":"59963